  "description": "A large-scale EEG dataset comprising 7,933 participants from India and Tanzania, collected through field-based research programs with nonspecialist teams. The dataset demonstrates that structured training and automated quality control enable reliable EEG data collection in diverse, non-laboratory settings across populations ranging from hunter-gatherers to office workers. Participant metadata include age, sex, income, and Mental Health Quotient scores, with data quality comparable to controlled laboratory benchmarks.",
  "methods_description": "EEG data were collected by trained nonspecialist research teams over a 30-week period in India and Tanzania. Data quality was assessed using PREP and FASTER methods on 5,831 records. Source EDF files were converted to BIDS format using MNE-BIDS. Participants completed surveys and assessments alongside EEG recording.",
